                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>necessary, always go as far as our <hi rend=\"underline\">Shulchan Aruch </hi>and\n                    <persName>Maimonides</persName> go.<lb/> That is the boundary, As far as which\n                I, as a learned man who under-<lb/>stands to read between the lines, must follow\n                with his spirit. That<lb/> is self-evident. I tell you if nothing happens for\n                Conservative Ju-<lb/>daism, everything is lost, and all, except those who now life\n                in fear<lb/> of eternal punishment, will go over to the camp of the enemy.\n                Inside<lb/> the synagogue, they want to be called pious. Inside their houses,<lb/>\n                they eat trefah and violate the <date>Sabbath</date>. Here it is a terrible\n                thing<lb/> to see. Unfortunately, people do not understand how to “increase the<lb/>\n                Torah and glorify it”. You, too, refused to understand how to proceed<lb/> with\n                wisdom and intelligence. If you do understand how to accomplish<lb/> much, it does\n                not seem to be on the practical side. Unfortunately,<lb/> the statement of the great\n                    <persName>Rabba</persName> is not sufficiently well-known.<lb/> “He who forgoes\n                his own qualities, all his sins are removed.”</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">When people who do not know the words of our sages, mis-<lb/>take\n                the unessential for the essential„ I do not hold it against them.<lb/> They know no\n                better. It is preferable that they should hold on to<lb/> the unessential in order\n                that he essential should not be forgotten.<lb/> But when one sees that the important\n                ones of <placeName>Israel</placeName> throw the Torah<lb/> overboard and maintain\n                silly customs only for the sake of gain, only<lb/> to act hypocritically, then one\n                must weep for the destruction of our<lb/> holy Torah. These people do not know and\n                do not understand what it<lb/> means, “Desecrate one <date>Sabbath</date> in order\n                that you may be able to observe<lb/> many <date>Sabbaths</date>”. I can tell you for\n                your own satisfaction, you, the<lb/> Portuguese who has cast aside the comments of\n                    <persName>Rabbi Moses Isserlein</persName><lb/> (RaMA) which are holy to me,\n                that in my small community, <hi rend=\"underline\">Emunei Israel</hi>,<lb/> I have had\n                recited the counting of the <hi rend=\"underline\">Omer</hi>.... on the other hand,\n                I<lb/> insist that there be no idle conversation, no business talk, and such<lb/>\n                like.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I will not say about myself that I have a fuller insight</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32z1392w/canvas/p2"
                }
